<section class="about-story" aria-label="Our story">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <p>WAI-ME started in May 2013, at the Dubai Airport Show, under the patronage of His Highness Sheikh Ahmed bin Saeed Al Maktoum. That October, a small group of women held the first board meeting and committed to building a Middle East chapter of Women in Aviation International. In November 2014, WAI International formally recognised the chapter, and we have operated continuously since, in association with The Emirates Aerosports Federation in Dubai.</p>
        <p>In the years since, we have shown up where the industry gathers, at the Dubai Airshow, the Abu Dhabi Air Expo, MEBAA, the Airport Show in Dubai, the Global Aerospace Summit, and the Kuwait Aviation Show, and our annual conference has grown into one of the region's cornerstone events for women in aviation. By 2019 it drew more than 750 attendees, 26 international speakers, and a dozen sponsor companies. We have grown from a handful of founding members in 2013 to more than 1,300 members across the Middle East and beyond.</p>
      </div>
